creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit
                <date>2012-03-06T15:17-0500</date>

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value:
Howard Brubaker was an editor (
                <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">Success</title> and 
                <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">Liberator</title>) and a contributor to many other periodicals from 1918 through the 1950's, including: 
                <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">Collier's</title>, 
                <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">The New Yorker</title>, 
                <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">The New Republic</title>, and 
                <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">Saturday Evening Post</title>. Many of his contributions were political in nature and reflected his, at times, left-of-center point of view. The collection includes his manuscripts and copies of journals to which he contributed. Brubaker died in 1957.

p.value: Open to researchers. Appointments are necessary for the use of manuscript and archival materials.

Published citations should take the following form:

                <address>
                    <addressline>Fales Library and Special Collections</addressline>
                </address>, New York University Libraries.
Series VI consists of a single box of oversized materials.
